{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01VJ61HNUDRrga7zfxmD2BZo","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Both criteria are met:\n- Without `X-Feature` header → `stable`\n- With `X-Feature: v2` → `canary`\n\n**What was wrong and what I fixed:**\n\nThe `canary-canary` Ingress had its annotations misconfigured — it was matching on `X-Canary: beta` instead of `X-Feature: v2`. I patched two annotations with `kubectl annotate --overwrite`:\n\n| Annotation | Before | After |\n|---|---|---|\n| `nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/canary-by-header` | `X-Canary` | `X-Feature` |\n| `nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/canary-by-header-value` | `beta` | `v2` |\n\nThe `nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/canary: \"true\"` annotation was already present, so nginx-ingress treats this Ingress as a canary overlay on top of `canary-stable`. Requests matching the header go to `canary-echo`; all others fall through to `stable-echo`."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":215,"cache_read_input_tokens":33304,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":215},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f2908436-8012-446f-8686-602f4d5f1358","uuid":"9efd2154-ba18-4d0b-9e95-3093e82aaa2e","request_id":"req_011CcN5Jc6reSA4EvBLnRDJ8"}
